meanings.definition: To increase the operating speed of a computer's central processing unit (CPU) beyond the manufacturer's recommended limits.
meanings.sent1: He overclocked his computer to make it faster.
meanings.sent2: She successfully overclocked her CPU for better performance.
meanings.sent3: The computer felt proud after being overclocked to work faster.
meanings.sent4: Her determination overclocked the speed of her computer like a rocket.
meanings.sent5: Overclocking the CPU was like giving the computer a turbo boost.
